-- Colombian bank Grupo Aval expects to raise $1.1 bln in US IPO
-- 
-- Mon Sep 08, 2014 11:07AM EDT
-- None



Sept 8 (Reuters) - Grupo Aval <GAA.CN>, Colombia's largest banking conglomerate, said it expects to raise $1.1 billion through an initial public offering in the United States.

The group said it expects to list its American Depositary Shares (ADSs) on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol "AVAL".